{"id":"stars","term":"Stars","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>The eleven stars (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 37:9\">Gen. 37:9</a>); the seven (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Amos 5:8\">Amos 5:8</a>); wandering (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jude 1:1\">Jude 1</a>:13); seen in the east at the birth of Christ, probably some luminous meteors miraculously formed for this specific purpose (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 2:2\">Matt. 2:2-10</a>); stars worshipped (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 4:19\">Deut. 4:19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 17:16\">2 Kings 17:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 21:3\">21:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 19:13\">Jer. 19:13</a>); spoken of symbolically (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 24:17\">Num. 24:17</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 1:16\">Rev. 1:16</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:20\">20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 12:1\">12:1</a>). (See ASTROLOGERS.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 37:9","Amos 5:8","Jude 1:1","Matthew 2:2","Deuteronomy 4:19","2 Kings 17:16","2 Kings 21:3","Jeremiah 19:13","Numbers 24:17","Revelation 1:16","Genesis 1:20","Genesis 12:1"]}